The paper focuses on using deep neural networks for skin disease diagnosis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests the paper may fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The large-scale dataset collection and comparison of classifiers may also suggest multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
